23: The minimum wage in Germany has been in the spotlight of public debate for many years. There has been a lively debate on the possible economic consequences of introducing a statutory minimum wage, especially for employment. In addition, there has been a discussion about who would be affected by a statutory minimum wage and how it would affect these workers' earnings.

24: In a recent study, we analyze the distribution of hourly wages and the effects of the introduction of the statutory minimum wage in Germany using data from the Socio-Economic Panel (SOEP) (Fuest and Potrafke 2020). The SOEP is an annual survey of more than 20,000 households in Germany. Since 1984 the SOEP has covered a wide range of topics, including demographics, labor market participation, income, and assets (Wagner et al. 2007).
